  "description": "<section id=\"description\">\n<p>A positive integer with $k$ (decimal) digits is called balanced if its first $⌈\\frac{k}{2}⌉$ digits sum to the same value as its last $⌈\\frac{k}{2}⌉$ digits, where $⌈x⌉$, pronounced ceiling of $x$, is the smallest integer $≥ x$, thus $⌈π⌉ = 4$ and $⌈5⌉ = 5$.</p>\n<p>So, for example, all palindromes are balanced, as is 13722.</p>\n<p>Let $T(n)$ be the sum of all balanced numbers less than $10^n$.</p>\n<p>Thus: $T(1) = 45$, $T(2) = 540$ and $T(5) = 334\\,795\\,890$.</p>\n<p>Find $T(47)\\,mod\\,3^{15}$</p>\n</section>",
